  "riddle": "1. Uncover the neighborhood that proudly preserves its architectural tale, once home to stylish abodes — what year did this charming enclave rise?\n\n2. Seek the compilation of places where history whirls, marked by dedication and preservation — how many tongues articulate their stories?\n\n3. A landmark moment unfolded when a significant act aimed to safeguard the past — which legislative assembly ushered in this important measure?\n\n4. Journey to where congressional decisions are made and discover how high it stands above the sea — what is the elevation of the assembly that enacted your previous answer?\n\n5. Nearby recreational areas flourish around this assembly — how many parks call the vicinity of this congress their home?\n\n6. To gauge the preservation's impact, calculate the difference between the elevation from clue 4 and the count of parks from clue 5. What result emerges?\n\n7. A remarkable fair once illuminated a vibrant city's spirit — find the geographical markers that tell where this historic event transpired.\n\n8. Count the sacred havens that grace the neighborhood surrounding this iconic exhibition site. What is their number?\n\n9. When traversing the distance from the place of the fallen leader's memorial to Omaha, how far in miles will the journey take you?\n\n10. Delve into the details of this distance — how many 1-bits populate the binary representation of your driving distance found in clue 9?\n\n11. In the annals of baseball, a team triumphed in many cities — can you remember the early stadiums that hosted this legendary franchise, along with their corresponding years?\n\n12. Reflecting on the team's legacy, how many vowels parade through the name of this storied baseball club?\n\n13. To appreciate the essence of a game, seek out the very measurements of the cushioned bases — what are their sides and thickness?\n\n14. Within the realm of pitching mastery lies a player whose earned run average tells a tale of his accomplishments